cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a new imitation learning method that explicitly models the level of demonstrators' expertise with a probabilistic graphical model and estimates it along with a reward function. Additionally, the paper uses a variational approach, which is a common technique in machine learning. The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it tests the proposed method on continuous-control benchmarks. The paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category as it involves learning a policy from demonstrations. Computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant category as the proposed method could potentially be applied to vision-based imitation learning tasks. Finally, the paper may belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) category as it involves learning a control policy.
